      "content": "While ethnic identity is very visible in Nigerian politics, framing instability purely as \"tribalism\" is an oversimplification. Many underlying issues like socioeconomic inequality, competition for federal resources, and political marginalization fuel these tensions. These deeper structural problems often cause ethnic groups to mobilize around identity as a form of political leverage. Therefore, the conflict is often a collision of identity politics with resource scarcity and governance issues.",
